message.content:
1. There are three groups in the study: Group P2.5, Group P7.5, and Group P+D.
2. In Group P2.5, 49% of patients did not experience any nausea or vomiting throughout the study.
3. In Group P7.5, 67% of patients did not experience any nausea or vomiting throughout the study.
4. In Group P+D, 81% of patients did not experience any nausea or vomiting throughout the study.
5. The difference in the percentage of patients who did not experience any nausea or vomiting throughout the study among the three groups is statistically significant (P<0.01).
